org.hibernate.metamodel.model.relational.spi

Interface ForeignKey.ColumnMappings

  • Enclosing class:
    ForeignKey

    public static interface ForeignKey.ColumnMappings
    Models the metadata for a foreign key (physical or logical).

    The terms "target" and "referring" used here are relative to the direction of the FK. E.g. given a table ADDRESS that defines a foreign key referring to a PERSON table... ADDRESS would be the referencing table and PERSON would be the target table. The columns in ADDRESS making up the FK would be the referring columns, and the columns on the PERSON table (referred to by the FK) would be the target columns: 

    
     referring                target
     -----------------        ----------------------------
     ADDRESS             ->   PERSON
         PERSON_ID       ->       ID

    Note that this is made an interface to allow for variants of FK declaration to potentially provide dedicated impls. These variants include:

    • FKs that reference to the target table's PK and that name the columns the same
    • FKs that reference to the target table's PK and define them in the same order
    • FKs that reference to column(s) in the target table that are not its defined PK

    Note also that it is expected that the ColumnMappings have been validated prior to passing the in:

    • both sides define the same number of Columns
    • all referring Columns come from the referring Table and that all target Columns come from the target Table as defined by Column.getSourceTable()
